snippet.textDisplay: as a pakistani american, i actually get frustrated a lot with pakistans music scene. its either full of unoriginal western mimicking rock or soft delicate feminine flowery music that appeals more to women. Are there no culturally authentic types of music in pakistan with an appeal to men? Theres so much good punjabi music in india sung in punjabi or pashto music in afghanistan and kpk, but pakistan's music scene is either corny girly music or "rock/pop" desperately reeking of acceptance from western world, where are some drums some bass some loud songs with no lyrics in english? just my two cents
